{{native name|no|'''Altevatnet'''|nbsp=no}} or {{native name|se|'''Álddesjávri'''|nbsp=no}} is [[Norway]]’s [[List of lakes in Norway|11th largest lake]]. The {{convert|79.71|km2|adj=on}} lake lies in the [[Bardu Municipality]] in [[Troms]] county, Norway. The lake is the largest lake in the county. It is approximately {{convert|38|km}} long and about {{convert|2.5|km}} wide. The [[lake]] is regulated by a [[dam]] on the northwestern end of the lake. The surface lies {{convert|489|m}} above sea level and reaches a maximum depth of {{convert|99|m}} below the surface of the lake.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nve.no/no/vann-og-vassdrag/lengste-dypeste-storste-/de-storste-innsjoene-i-norge/|title=De største innsjøene i Norge|language=Norwegian|publisher=Norges vassdrags- og energidirektorat|date=2009-04-01|accessdate=2012-09-19|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120525111359/http://www.nve.no/no/Vann-og-vassdrag/Lengste-dypeste-storste-/De-storste-innsjoene-i-Norge/|archivedate=2012-05-25|df=|trans-title="The largest lakes in Norway"}}</ref>
The lake lies about {{convert|10|km}} from [[Sweden]] and it is located right between the two national parks: [[Øvre Dividal National Park]] and [[Rohkunborri National Park]]. The water discharges to the north into the [[Barduelva]] river, which empties into [[Målselva]] river, which in turn empties into the [[Malangen (fjord)|Malangen]] [[fjord]].<ref name="snl">{{cite web|url=http://snl.no/Altevatnet|title=Altevatnet|author=Store norske leksikon|authorlink=Store norske leksikon|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2012-09-19}}</ref>
